HEADWORD: Umbilic
<hw>Um*bil"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>umbilicus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ombilic</ets>. See
<er>Navel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The navel; the center.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>umbilic</xex> of the world.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir T. Herbert.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>An umbilicus. See
<er>Umbilicus</er>, 5 <sd>(b)</sd>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Umbilic</ent>⟦br⟧

